# Routing and Page Guidelines

## TanStack Router Setup
- Use TanStack Router for all routing
- Define routes in a centralized location
- Use type-safe route definitions
- Implement proper route guards where needed

## Page Components
- Keep pages focused on layout and composition
- Delegate complex logic to custom hooks
- Use proper loading states
- Implement error boundaries
- Handle route parameters safely

## Best Practices
- Keep pages lightweight
- Use lazy loading for routes
- Implement proper meta tags
- Handle 404 and error states
- Use proper TypeScript types for route params
